com.crawljax.core.configuration

Class CrawljaxConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.crawljax.core.configuration.CrawljaxConfiguration

  • public final class CrawljaxConfiguration
extends Object
    Specifies the settings Crawljax. The methods in this class fall into two categories:Oz

    • General properties of Crawljax
    • Properties for the crawling setCrawlSpecification(CrawlSpecification)
    DEFAULT VAlUES: Browser: webdriver firefox Project Full Path: empty Project Relative Path: empty Filter attributes: closure_hashcode_(\\w)*, jquery[0-9]+ Test invariants while crawling: true EXAMPLE: CrawljaxConfiguration crawljaxConfig = new CrawljaxConfiguration(); CrawlSpecification crawler = new CrawlSpecification("http://www.google.com"); crawler.click("a"); crawljaxConfig.setCrawlSpecification(crawler);
    Version:
    $Id$

      • addPlugin

        public void addPlugin(Plugin plugin)
        Add a plugin to the execution. Note that the order of adding is the same as running for the same type of plugin. This means that if you add a precrawling plugin p1 and next you add a precrawling plugin p2, p1 will be executed before p2.
        Parameters:
        plugin - Add a plugin. See Plugin.
